Descrição da Função

biosurfit is a Portuguese diagnostics company focused on the development and manufacture of IVD tests for the point-of-care market with highly innovative proprietary technology and dedicated to the provision of medical diagnostic services. As a certified laboratory, biosurfit offers different services in health care, from clinical analyses, exams, treatments, homecare services, among others. Additionally, the company created an online platform dedicated to the online commerce of products from supplements, self-tests, non-prescription Medicines (MNSRM) and others. We believe that everyone should have access to health and wellness services and products and thus contribute to improving their quality of life. In order to cover the different diagnostic services, biosurfit has created different brands that have been growing along with the company reinforcing its position in the health industry, always providing the best quality products and services. biosurfit is looking for a talented scientist to join its Research and Development team. The successful candidate will integrate a fast-paced multidisciplinary team in an innovative project for point-of-care diagnostics. The following skills are required for the post:


MsC or PhD in Biomedical Engineering, Biological Engineering, Biochemistry, Biotechnology, or a related field;
Solid knowledge of laboratory procedures, sample manipulation, and assay detection techniques (Spectrophotometry, Microscopy, Chromatography, Fluorescence);
Basic understanding of microfluidics, experience on design and prototyping is a plus;
Knowledge of surface treatment and coating techniques is a plus;
Proficiency in data analysis and statistics; knowledge of R or Python is a plus;
Dynamic, pro-active, and hands-on approach to tasks and challenges;
Exceptional team-working and communication skills;
Autonomy and organization, with the ability to work with minimal supervision;
Analytical thinking and a problem-solving attitude. Responsibilities (training will be provided where necessary):
Development of new point-of-care diagnostics assays and other quantitative assay applications;
Integration/adaptation of benchtop procedures into microfluidic devices, evaluation of assay compatibility, prototype validation and transfer to manufacture;
Data analysis, providing technical input and solutions for project challenges, and progress reporting;
Direct contact with internal and external partners to ensure design transfer for assay applications;
Compliance with regulatory requirements for R&D projects;
When required, assistance with other existing projects. Workplace: Azambuja Localização
